               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 5ra-21rb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 21va-46va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     46vb-133ra)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 46vb-59vb)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 60va-63rb), preceded by an excerpt
                     from “The Book of the Testament” (fol. 60ra-va)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 63ra-72vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, son of Thunder (fols. 72vb-80va)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 80vb-87vb)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Athanasius of
                     Alexandria (fols. 87vb-97va)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus
                     (fols. 97va-103rb)
 III-8) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols.
                     103va-108ra)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fols. 108ra-113ra)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of
                     Alexandria (fols. 113ra-114vb)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug
                     (fols. 114vb-119va)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols.
                     119va-126rb)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     126rb-130vb)
 III-14) Second Anaphora of St Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of
                     St Gregory”) (fols. 130vb-133ra)
 IV) Ṣalota ʿǝṭān “Prayer of the Incense”
                     (fols. 133ra-140rb)
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text IV is written in smaller script than the previous three
                        texts.</note>
                     <note>Spaces for the names of the reigning King and church dignitaries in the
                        supplication formulas are either left blank or filled in with the word
                        እገሌ፡.</note>
                  </msItem>
