                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the
                           constituent texts; directives for the ministers; part of the musical
                           notation signs above the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of
                           decorated quire numbers; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic
                           numbers.
 
 The incipit parts of many of the constituent texts
                           are written alternately in red and black lines (s. fols. 5ra-rb, 72vb,
                           80vb, 87vb, etc.).</seg>
